@CMDX v1
@DICT{
  $0=https://api.example.com/v2
  $1=Parameters:
  $2=unique identifier
  $3=of the user
  $4=a JSON object containing
  $5=Rate Limits
}
@H1 User Management API

@P Base URL: @C{$0}

@P All requests require an @B{Authorization} header with a valid Bearer token. See @LINK{Authentication Guide>$0/docs/auth} for details.

@H2 Endpoints

@ENDPOINT{GET /users/{id}}

@P Retrieves a user by their $2.

@P @B{$1}

@PARAMS{
  id:string:R~The $2 $3
}

@P @B{Response:}

@P Returns $4 the user data:

@KV{
  id:string~The $2 $3
  name:string~Display name
  email:string~Primary email address
  role:string~One of: admin, user, viewer
  created_at:string~ISO 8601 timestamp
}

@ENDPOINT{POST /users}

@P Creates a new user account.

@P @B{$1}

@PARAMS{
  name:string:R~Display name
  email:string:R~Primary email address
  role:string:O~One of: admin, user, viewer. Default: user
}

@P @B{Response:}

@P Returns $4 the created user.

@ENDPOINT{DELETE /users/{id}}

@P Deletes a user by their $2.

@P @B{$1}

@PARAMS{
  id:string:R~The $2 $3
}

@P @B{Response:}

@P Returns $4 a confirmation message.

@NOTE{This action is irreversible. All user data will be permanently deleted.}

@H2 $5

@P All endpoints are subject to rate limiting. See @LINK{$5>$0/docs/rate-limits} for current limits.

@H2 Errors

@P All errors return $4:

@KV{
  code:string~Machine-readable error code
  message:string~Human-readable error description
  request_id:string~Unique identifier for the request
}
